SUMMARY:Annual Lunar New Year at Sonoma Community Center
DESCRIPTION:The Center celebrates Lunar New Year with vibrant cultural programming and hands-on workshops throughout February and March\, culminating in a special Community Day featuring live performances and family-friendly activities.    This free event includes traditional Chinese calligraphy presented by Sonoma Valley Council Member Jack Ding and Gigi Tan Pfleger\, a Chinese Mahjong demonstration\, and children’s crafts hosted by the Center’s Youth Arts Program. Guests can enjoy a variety of Bay Area AAPI food vendors and makers offering items for purchase. Live entertainment highlights include a dance performance by Hula Mai\, founded by Betty Ann Ka Ihilani Bruno\, followed by a performance from Redwood Empire Chinese Association\, dedicated to preserving and sharing Chinese culture\, language\, and heritage.
URL:https://www.sonoma.com/event/annual-lunar-new-year-at-sonoma-community-center/
LOCATION:276 East Napa Street, Sonoma, CA, 95476, United States
CATEGORIES:Celebration,Dancing,Family Friendly,Holiday,Performing Arts,Sonoma County
