SUMMARY:Black History Month at Left Edge Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Black History Month at Left Edge Theatre celebrates powerful storytelling with a production that blends wit\, spontaneity\, and emotional honesty. The play Proud to Present (abridged from its full title about the Herero of Namibia and German colonial history) is a meta-theatrical exploration of race\, privilege\, and the complexities of historical narrative. Six actors attempt to portray the genocide of the Herero people\, but the rehearsal evolves into a confrontation about perspective and the challenges of storytelling itself. Through moments that are both humorous and deeply moving\, the production invites reflection on history and human understanding.
URL:https://www.sonoma.com/event/black-history-month-at-left-edge-theatre/2026-03-07/
LOCATION:528 7th St. , Santa Rosa, CA, 95401, United States
CATEGORIES:Celebration,Holiday,Performing Arts,Sonoma County
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://winecountry-media.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2026/03/03194128/Screenshot-2026-03-03-213929.png
END:VEVENT
